This project analyzes the Bright Coffee Shop sales dataset, which contains daily transaction data from a coffe shop. The business appointed a new CEO to grow revenue and improve product perfomance.
As a junior analyst, l was assigned to extract actionable insights from historical data and prepare a presentation to support the CEO's decision- making.

The main objectives of this analysis are: Identify which products generate the most revenue, determine the best- performing times of the day, Analyze sales trends across products and time intervals and provides recomendations to improve overall sales performance.

Methodology
The analysis was conducted in the following steps:
Data cleaning
Removing duplicates
Handled missing values

Data Analysis: Queried data using SQL to extract key metrics and aggregated sales by product, time and category

Data visualization: createed pivot tables and charts in Excel 

Key Insights 
Certain products contribute the highest share of revenue
Peak sales occur during specific hours of the day, Some product categories perform consistently better than others and sales patterns vary across different time intervals

Summary
This project successfully analyzed coffee shop sales data to uncover trends in product performance. The insights generated can help the business to increase revenue.

Tools 
Miro
Canva
Databricks
Microsoft Excel
Powerpoint

